        "title": "feat(slides): add object-scoped text editing primitives",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add `gog slides style-text` for UTF-16 range-scoped text style updates on one objectId\n- add `gog slides link` for range-scoped hyperlink updates through Slides text style link fields\n- add `gog slides bullets` for CreateParagraphBullets/DeleteParagraphBullets on one objectId and range\n- extend `replace-text` with a safe object-scoped v1 path, or document and validate the v1 limitation if exact object replacement cannot be made safe in this PR\n\n## Release note\nAdds focused Slides text-editing commands for styling, links, bullets, and safer object-level replacement without changing the existing unscoped `replace-text` default.\n\n## Validation\n- `make test TEST_PKGS=./internal/cmd TEST_FLAGS='-run=TestSlides'`\n- `make fmt-check`\n- `make ci`\n\nThanks @sebsnyk for the report.\n\nFixes https://github.com/openclaw/gogcli/issues/823\n",
